> Say hello to miso! Umami is one of the five tastes used when tasting food. A staple in Japanese cuisine, miso is made from fermented soy bean paste and is typical of giving the umami flavour that tastebuds love.

== Pasta ==

Boil a full #kettle{}, then pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{1%drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Mushrooms and Bacon ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the @British Smoked Bacon Lardons{90%g} and @Sliced Mushrooms{120%g} to the pan.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook it thoroughly.

== Sauce ==

In the meantime, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the garlic to the pan and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir in the @Water for the Sauce{150%ml}, @Miso Paste{15%g} and @Wild Mushroom Paste{15%g}.

> If your wild mushroom paste has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @Creme Fraiche{150%g} and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}. Simmer for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Baby Spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the cooked pasta and @Butter{20%g}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash more water if you feel it needs it.

== To Serve ==

Share the creamy miso pasta between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!